author: bsummer4
title: Create a basic renderer with sdl.
date: 2009-11-13T21:59:59Z
status: resolved

Write a utility the allows for simple animations.  There are three
operations, load an image, draw an image on the screen, and update
(flip) the display.  Here is an example session:

    new Ben data/person.pgm
    new John data/person.pgm
    new Daniel data/person.pgm
    new Chris data/person.pgm
    new explosive data/explosive.pgm
    new map data/example.pgm
    draw map 0 0
    draw Ben 100 100
    draw Chris 300 300
    draw explosive 200 200
    flip
    draw map 0 0
    draw Ben 100 100
    draw Chris 300 300
    draw John 200 200
    flip
    draw explosive 100 100
    flip
    draw map 0 0
    draw Chris 300 300
    draw John 200 200
    draw Daniel 210 210
    flip
    draw explosive 300 300
    flip
    draw map 0 0
    draw John 200 200
    draw Daniel 210 210
    flip
    draw map 0 0
    draw John 300 300
    draw Daniel 310 310
    flip
    draw map 0 0
    draw John 400 400
    draw Daniel 410 410
    flip
    draw map 0 0
    draw John 500 500
    draw Daniel 510 510
    flip
    draw map 0 0
    flip


